"""Shared social-network catalog — the single source of truth for which networks
the brand can display and share to.

SOCIAL_LINKS_KMS_SYNC_PLAN (2026-07-11). Consumed by:
  - CMS Settings → Social Links tab (via GET /api/meta/social-catalog → frontend/src/lib/socialCatalog.js mirror)
  - the public website Footer/Navbar (same endpoint)
  - the KMS (backend/kms/core.brand_social_links + base.html footer + post.html share row)

Design rules baked in from the rulings:
  - `share_url` is None for DISPLAY-ONLY networks (no public web share-intent endpoint).
    D1: display-only networks NEVER render in a sharing section — only as brand/follow links.
  - `share` keys MUST match the existing /share-track slugs so the Member-Points engine keeps
    counting without a migration: facebook, x, linkedin, whatsapp, pinterest (see plan §5).
  - `label` is a proper noun — no translation (same string EN/ES). D7: the payment app is "CashMe".

Icon markup (`svg`) is the INNER markup of a 16×16 `viewBox="0 0 16 16"` icon (paths only),
so every surface can wrap it in its own <svg> with its own sizing/color (currentColor).
Networks without a bespoke brand glyph fall back to GENERIC_SVG (a neutral link glyph); brand
fidelity for those is a Phase-4 walk-through polish item, not a functional dependency.
"""

